  "description": "This dataset contains somatosensory MEG recordings converted to BIDS format, including anatomical MRI data and derived FreeSurfer segmentations. The dataset includes preprocessed forward models and boundary element models suitable for source localization studies. It serves as a reference implementation for MEG-MRI co-registration and BIDS conversion workflows.",
  "methods_description": "MEG data were acquired during somatosensory stimulation. Anatomical T1-weighted MRI was processed using FreeSurfer's recon-all pipeline with default parameters, followed by scalp surface generation and watershed-based boundary element modeling. Forward models were computed using source space definitions, head-MRI transforms derived from anatomical landmarks, and conductor models.",
